<br>
Went something like this:<br>
&quot;So you think your a bad ass huh? (get right up close to them) You feel the need to impress your friends by beating on somebody smaller than you , Huh? (Get closer) &quot;Okay then, come on let's show just how bad you are&quot;<br>
<br>
And you get your ass beat.<br>
<br>
After a couple of times they start avoiding you. In a matter of fact I had a few of them turning around and taking off when they see me by shouting &quot;There you are, come on we got unfinished business!&quot;<br>
<br>
Worked for me, and the scars and lumps go away after a few years.<br>
<br>
-Stryven <p>Searching for Mommy for 19 (Oops, back to 18)(Hey, back to 19)(Damn! 18 again)(19?) seasons now</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mysteweave>Mysteweave</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 359<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/19/03 5:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3896.topic&index=22>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: You aren't going to like this suggestion....</span><hr size=1> *snugs Stryven* *sigh*<br>
<br>
There's no easy answers in this, and the reason is, different people react differently. Some people, if you ignore them and their bullying react by torturing you further, because you suffer in silence -- they get off on making you feel bad, and they know they are doing it, and don't care if you react. On the other hand, if you react, there are some bullies who like this response and the attention they get, and it will just perpetuate. You'll have to make your decision based on experience and knowledge of those involved.<br>
<br>
But I will say you're not the only one who was ever tortured by fellow school-mates, physically and mentally. My high-school bussing experience was the most tramatic experience I had of the day for the most part. It made getting up and going to school every day the most dreaded experience in my life. I was already having problems at home -- and I was severely depressed. To have fellow bus-riders attack me, call me names, belittle and berate me throughout the 45 minutes it took to get to school in the morning and home in the afternoon was just too much. It was horrible, demorializing and has helped to make me the insecure person I am today. I'm not entirely sure what I did, or what I said or how I behaved that made people do this to me. There was just a little group of them all that seemed to get off on walking on me. Only one thing tempered it a little bit -- my friendship with one of the buss riders named Brett. They all liked him, and one day he had to sit with me -- and found out we had a lot in common. (No he'd never taken part in the harassment either). So when he sat with me, they'd pretty much leave me alone -- and after a while it seems he sat with or by me every day -- so I think he realized that his presence had a halting effect on the situation. This was junior year and sophomore years of highschool. <br>
<br>
Senior year, he had graduated the year before <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . So unfortunately he was no longer there -- and we had a new crop of buttheads who decided they'd take part and join in on the fun. However, my sister -- who was a freshman that year took heavy umbrage at my being attacked and felt it reflected on her. We eventually had to petition for a bus-change and wound up walking an extra 5 minutes to another corner to take a different bus to school. Things got better after that. But that wasn't the end of it -- these people were still at school with me, and one of the fellows who rode the bus also worked with me after school and carried it on there -- don't know why we never got fired <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <br>
<br>
All I can say is hold your chin up and keep telling yourself it doesnt' matter and don't believe anything they say. Or: Make a joke out of it. <br>
<br>
