My way is to be friendly--if someone thinks I am a pushover they will think twice before I am through with them, but it's because my resources are my allies.  It's kinda hard to single a person out in a crowd.  Make friends with people.  I was very cynical when I came into High school, my middle school friends didn't all mesh well with me.<br>
Then there was this girl that was always saying comments like:  I love your hair or that is such a great shirt.<br>
Because of my previous friends I mistook her attitude to be sarcasm.  She was sincere.  Well as soon as I saw that I totally changed my attitude toward her.  She talked and dressed different and never got teased because she gave out <br>
&quot;honey&quot; instead of &quot;vinegar.&quot;  Instead she got friends in return for her admiring compliments.<br>
Sure you could beat people up, but I had friends that were like that and they didn't finish school, they didn't even make it to High school with me.  So I would go for making friends with people who deserve your company.  It it is nice to have some sympathy on your peer level.<br>
But keep in mind that now is your chance to develop a strategy to combat this problem cuz it will keep coming up in life.<br>
