Meet 'John'.  See, I lived in Georgia but moved to Pennsylvania during my 10th grade year.  The old, historical town I live in now has serious issues, esepcially with people that didn't grow up here.  So when show up in mid september, I was talking to this nice redhead girl (we're good friends now) and some fucking football player throws me up against the lockers tells me something like &quot;and stay the fuck away from her&quot;.  I kinda sat there for a second, the laughing subsided, the crowd dissipated, I picked up that fucking thick ap european history book, thought about slamming it in his face.  thought better of it.    <br>
<br>
So now the guy recognizes me and harrases me on a daily basis.  I take a long way between third and fourth mod to avoid him, he eventually finds me and harassment continues. <br>
<br>
December.  I worked at the ski resort (popularity points, good bonuses too) and tried out ski blading, the short death-wish skis.  They were a blast, I love anything that gives me adrenaline, and I wasn't half bad.  I buy my own pair and join the ski club.  Well, the winter wasn't to bad during december '02, but it still iced up pretty bad after a night of sleet, and the entire surface of freakin central PA was a sheet of ice.  (yes, they still ran school buses), I step off the bus in the morning, I've got my backpack on one shoulder and my heavy duffel-style bag with my ski blades, boots, and ski pants on the other shoulder.  Now I'm not exactly Mr. Coordinated, so I'm guessing you can vision what happens next.  Most people are standing around outside, in the snow and light sleet, like always, because the school won't open it's doors until 7:00, I go to step off bus and..<br>
<br>
my chin hit the frozen curb with such velocity that I chipped two teeth, split my bottom lip, and had a pretty deep cut in my chin.  There was blood everywhere pretty instantly.  Well, &quot;john&quot; was right there to witness it all, he pointed, said it was gnarly at first, but then started his usually bullying routine.  All the blood rushing to my face, I was beet red, and my eyes started to tear up, not from pain but from a combo of embarassment and adrenaline.  Well, I opened my ski bag and took the towel out that I wrapped around my ski's after every use, to keep them from rusting and just keep them nice (they're friggin expensive!), I was holding the towel to my face, left my bookbag and threw my duffel bag over my shoulder, tried to walk around him and his croonies but they moved into my way.  it was obivious they didn't intend for me to get to the front of the school, so I suddenly had quite an enlightenment.  The edges of the skis are really sharp, for carving turns on the slopes, so what'd I do?  Well, acted like I was putting the towel away in the bag, with my back turned to him, pulled a ski from my bag, swung around and hit him square in the face with the thing.  His buddies beat the shit out of me, but he had a &quot;gnarly&quot; scab and later light scar for the whole year.  He had to get 14 stitches, the ski lashed from his right ear to his mouth corner.  <br>
So his buddies beat me up pretty bad that day, but he never came close to me the rest of the year, and even now.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
